race.comment: Lots of these are making up the numbers. NETWORK ERROR (9) is an interesting runner who had his first try anti-clockwise last time when winding up strongly for fourth. Will be better for that and draw for a good run. Expected to go close. VERY GRATEFUL (4) is the clear threat. Finished eighth fresh over 1200m but this is a far better set-up. Comes through a strong form reference and strips fitter for an ideal journey now. Has the inside and the claim and gets a chance at an overdue win. ELVIS (1) tried to lead throughout last time but was claimed late and placed. Expected to give a sight again. IRISH BLISS (3) is on the quick back-up since finishing seventh last time. Races on speed and can give a sight again.
